The climate data, painstakingly collected, paints a picture of a place where 'mild' is a relative term and 'winter' is a lifestyle. One can observe the distinct trends in temperature and [precipitation](/Precipitation), noting how the oceanic influence, while preventing extreme cold, ensures a consistent, if not always gentle, dampness and an abundance of snow for the better part of the year. Truly, a place for those who appreciate the subtle nuances of perpetual chill.

